I think we need to diferenciate between the leaders and vips of our various alliances who can drum up a group easily and go hunt in a specific place for armor and the poor grunts who wait for a chance to go somewhere when its posted on their own guild boards or on the fed boards.<br>
<br>
As part of this federation we have a responsibility to the people who follow us to take them to the places where they can better themselves, I've been to dozens of kael raids and the drops in fear eclipse them in number with ease, I don't think even rallos zek has seen 3 bps drop on a kael raid.<br>
<br>
If we go on a fear raid and 50% of the items rot as everyone has better I'll stop going to fear for armor but thats not happened yet and I don't think it will for a good while.<br>
<br>
Not every guild in the fed has the manpower or classes to do the plate cycle or arena solo in their spare time but we don't need to do anything solo, we don't need individual guilds to be responsible for outfiting their people in order to come on our raids - we are friends, we are allies, we fight live and die together and we can have someone lead kael raids as well as plan fear raids.<br>
<br>
There are lots of reasons for going to a zone, epics, armor, fun, challenges, experience, adventure - take one element out of the equation and you still have all the others<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Eldark<br>
